recordings.loc: Peat Ponds Wildlife Area, Fairbanks-North Star Borough, Alaska
recordings.rmk: natural vocalization; begging calls from an older juvenile bird following an adult.  The habitat was a marshy pond on a reclaimed peat mine.  The chick was about 3/4 the size of the adult, and gave the louder begging calls every time the adult surfaced with food, and then the quieter ones while the adult bird was under water, or immediately after it was fed.

recordings.rmk: Horned Grebe giving alarm or distress call, struggling, while being held by the wing by an adult Great Blue Heron.  The heron had waited without moving for about 5 minutes at the inner edge of a rocky breakwater at Richmond Bay Marina. The grebe escaped, losing 2 or more primary feathers.  The heron gave two calls as the grebe escaped.   This recording was made while I was sitting on a sand spit within 50 feet of the birds.
